# .semgrepignore — default scan-TARGET exclusions for the semgrep extension.
#
# This controls what semgrep SCANS by default when a caller does not override
# the target selection. It does NOT affect the vendored rules in rules/vendor/
# or the custom rules in rules/custom/ — those are rule CONFIGS, not scan
# targets, and are always loaded explicitly via --config.
#
# Callers can still point semgrep_scan at any path explicitly; these globs only
# prune noise (dependencies, build artifacts, minified bundles, test specs)
# from directory scans.

# Dependencies
node_modules/

# Build / output artifacts
dist/
build/
.next/

# Minified bundles (not meaningful to audit; huge and noisy)
**/*.min.js

# Test / spec files (not production attack surface)
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.js
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts
